Even though in monotheistic religions, the God is considered to represent love, there are often [[angel]]s or similar beings that represent love as well.
  +
* [[Haniel (archangel)|Haniel]] — Angel of Venus in Judeo-Christian theology.

Various angels in Judeo-Christian angelic lore are also angels of love, for example: Donquel, Rahmiel, [[Raphael]] and Theliel.
